Gantz Reika Cosplay Lycoris (TEST Version)

I'm experimenting with LoCon parameters for attire and concept, depending on your model / prompt might hit or miss a lot. Recommended to lower weight at 0.55-0.65 for realistic model, for anime you can safely go at higher weight, test shows bad result at higher weight for realistic model (terrible hands, sketchy images, extra limbs), see trigger guide below for more detail.

Works best with FantasticMix model. ( v2.0 is better imo )

fantasticmix_real - v3.0 | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai

Key trigger are : gzrk
There are 3 trigger version of the bodysuit (do not combine version, will results in inaccurate clothing):

  1. full bodysuit trigger = bodysuit / black bodysuit / latex bodysuit (choose 1 only) -- recommended weight = 0.55-0.75 (0.75 only if bodysuit not showing correctly)

  2. leotard bodysuit trigger = leotard / black leotard / latex leotard, (choose 1 only), can be combined with: underboob, thigh strap, black thighhighs. -- recommended weight = 0.55-0.65

  3. sexy bodysuit trigger = revealing clothes, underboob, thigh strap, black thighhighs. --- recommended weight = 0.5 - 0.6

For best result use Dynamic CFG Threshold:

  • Mimic = 10 | Clamp Percentile 99.5

  • Min. Mimic Scale = 0, Cosine Up

  • CFG Scale Sch. = 15, Half Cosine Down

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

Please leave a review if you have any critiques or if you find this LoRa good.

Lazy Square style LoCon

—Ñ–∞–π–ª –Ω–∞ civitai—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∏—Ü–∞ –Ω–∞ civitai

In order to use the lycoris model you will need to install this extension https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-lycoris and use it inside your prompt according to readme or with another extension - additional networks.

It can do both, the original style and the one with chromatic aberration, just use the tags accordingly.

You may want or not to remain original eye style, just prompt white eyes inside the positive or negative. If you still getting generations with this eyes even in the negative prompt just define eye color explicitly inside pos prompt like {red|yellow|blue|green} eyes or so.

Art - Meirzhan Nurgozhin

—Ñ–∞–π–ª –Ω–∞ civitai—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∏—Ü–∞ –Ω–∞ civitai

Meirzhan Nurgozhin is absolutely one of the greatest artists in 2020 time. His artwork recorded the various views in time of the border countries between Russia and Mongolia.

His work are mainly oil painting, dry and thick brushes on canvas.

Not on details, what Meirzhan captured and expressed are the time, feeling and atmosphere.

His typical artworks -roughly interpreted- "the boy on the fence", "boy riding white lamb", "girl in red shoes" recorded the activities, living styles of people, children regardless of the difficult environment in extreme weather.

This model is merely a touch on the surface of his fantastic art works. It is strongly recommended to visit his site in Artstation. Can purchase the print of his work. https://mirzhan.artstation.com

It is not possible to exactly re-produce his dry brush oil painting style, even with PLMS sampler.

His artwork in low res 400x400 attached, 40 repeats.

Kohya_ss config: 2 batch, 2 epoch, net dim, alpha, conv dim, alpha 16,16, 8,1.

This is a model of silent movie actress Lillian Gish. It was made as an experiment in training a model on a limited dataset of mainly low quality black and white photos. It is not as good as I would like with the following issues:

tendency to generate red, blue, both, or purple highlights in hair (fixable for further revisions)

tendency to generate red, blue, or purple hair if hair colour unspecified (fixable for further revisions)

tendency to generate desaturated photos if the negative tag "monochrome" is not used (not fixable for further revisions, is due to the grayscale nature of the dataset)

Please do not generate anything disrespectful to her or her memory with my model, thank you.
